The paper deals with designing learning algorithms for discrete losses, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses statistical and computational complexity, which are important aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted on real datasets involve computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and learning rates, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
